This paper deals with machine learning models for sequence labeling and segmentation, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of natural language processing (NLP), computer vision (CV), and speech recognition. The paper also introduces a novel model structure that improves performance on these tasks, which is relevant to the sub-field of machine learning (ML) and specifically, structured prediction models. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
